  "base_path": "/correct-marriage-registration",
  "content_id": "cea526cf-bb4e-496a-ae46-9ba87c37e114",
  "description": "If there are any errors on a marriage or civil partnership certificate you can correct the original registration with the register office or GRO - find out what corrections can be made, who can apply, how long it takes, what they look like",
  "details": {
    "external_related_links": [

    ],
    "hide_chapter_navigation": false,
    "parts": [
      {
        "body": "<p>Corrections can only be made when the information in a marriage or civil partnership register is wrong (for example a mistake was made when recording a person’s occupation).</p>\n\n<p>You cannot apply for a correction to show new information if circumstances change after the marriage or civil partnership.</p>\n\n<p>You’ll need to find out if the mistake was made in the original registration or just on the certificate.</p>\n\n<p>To do this, <a href=\"/register-offices\">contact the register office</a> in the area where your marriage or civil partnership was registered. You need to contact the register office, even if your ceremony was held in another venue.</p>\n",
        "slug": "what-corrections-can-be-made",
        "title": "What corrections can be made"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>Either of the 2 people who married each other or formed a civil partnership can apply for a correction.</p>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If neither spouse or partner is alive, a correction will not be authorised.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2 id=\"if-the-mistake-is-only-on-the-marriage-or-civil-partnership-certificate\">If the mistake is only on the marriage or civil partnership certificate</h2>\n\n<p>If the details in the register are correct, and the mistake was made when copying the details from the register onto the certificate, you can <a href=\"/order-copy-birth-death-marriage-certificate\">order a new copy of the certificate</a>.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"if-the-mistake-is-in-the-original-registration\">If the mistake is in the original registration</h2>\n\n<p>You’ll need to apply to the register office in the area where the marriage or civil partnership was registered, even if the ceremony was held in another venue.</p>\n\n<p>It costs £90 to apply.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"/register-offices\">Contact the register office</a> to find out how to send your application and how to pay.</p>\n\n<p>Fill in the <a href=\"/government/publications/application-form-to-correct-details-on-a-marriage-registration\">application form to correct details on a marriage or civil partnership registration</a> and send it to the register office.</p>\n\n<p>The original information will always be shown in the register. After the correction has been authorised, a note will be added to the margin of the register. This will explain what the correct information is and when the correction was made.</p>\n\n<p>Any correction to a marriage or civil partnership entry needs to be authorised by the General Register Office (<abbr title=\"General Register Office\">GRO</abbr>) before it goes ahead.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"proving-the-record-is-wrong\">Proving the record is wrong</h3>\n\n<p>You’ll need to provide original documents or <a href=\"/certifying-a-document\">certified documents</a> to show what the correct information should have been at the time of the marriage or civil partnership.</p>\n\n<p>Send them to the register office in the area where the marriage or civil partnership was registered. They will then forward copies to <abbr title=\"General Register Office\">GRO</abbr>. This prevents your original documents from getting lost in the post.</p>\n\n<p>The documents should have been valid at the time of the marriage or civil partnership, or just before. You cannot use documents from after the date of the marriage or civil partnership to make a correction to an entry.</p>\n\n<p>Documents you can send in include a:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>passport</li>\n  <li>photocard driving licence</li>\n  <li>bank, building society or credit card statement dated within 3 months before the marriage or civil partnership</li>\n  <li>letter from a hospital or doctor</li>\n  <li>letter from a government department</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you cannot send in proof, corrections cannot usually be made.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>All certified copies sent with the application will be destroyed if you do not ask for them to be returned.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"how-long-applications-take\">How long applications take</h3>\n\n<p>There is not a set time for how long applications will take. It can take up to 25 days for you to get a reply.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"after-the-correction-has-been-approved\">After the correction has been approved</h3>\n\n<p>You’ll be told when the <abbr title=\"General Register Office\">GRO</abbr> has approved the correction.</p>\n\n<p>After that, you can <a href=\"/order-copy-birth-death-marriage-certificate\">buy a new marriage or civil partnership certificate</a> that shows the original information along with a note of the corrected details.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"advice\">Advice</h2>\n\n<p>If you want further advice on applying to make a correction, <a href=\"/register-offices\">contact the register office</a> where your marriage or civil partnership took place.</p>\n\n",
        "slug": "apply-to-correct-a-mistake",
        "title": "Apply to correct a mistake"
      }
    ]
  },
